value.value: A c-myc protein isoform 1 phosphorylated form in which the phosphorylation occurs at Ser residues of the Myc box I in the amino-terminal regulatory domain by activation of ROCK proteins through Ras signaling pathway. Example: UniProtKB:P01106-1, Ser-62/Ser-71, MOD:00046.

label.value: cartilage oligomeric matrix protein isoform 1, signal peptide removed form

value.value: A cartilage oligomeric matrix protein isoform 1 that has had the signal peptide removed to yield the mature protein.
A CREB-binding protein isoform 1 methylated form that has been methylated at arginine residues within the KIX domain. Example: UniProtKB:P45481-1, Arg-600/Arg-624, MOD:00658.
A fungal/metazoan cullin-1 isoform 1 neddylated form that has been neddylated in the conserved Lys residue within the IVR[ILV]MKxR[RK] motif. Example: UniProtKB:Q13616-1, Lys-720, MOD:01150.

label.value: cyclin-dependent kinase 4 inhibitor B isoform 1 phosphorylated 1

value.value: A cyclin-dependent kinase 4 inhibitor B isoform 1 phosphorylated form in which the phosphorylation occurs on a residue equivalent to Thr-12 of the amino acid sequence represented by UniProtKB:P55271-1. Example: UniProtKB:P55271-1, Thr-12, MOD:00047.
A decorin isoform A, signal peptide removed form that has been processed by subsequent removal of the propeptide, rendering the mature decorin protein core.

label.value: decorin isoform A cleaved and glycosylated 1

value.value: A decorin isoform A cleaved and glycosylated form that has been modified with O-linked glycosaminoglycan at the most N-terminal SG site and additional N-linked glycosylated Asn residues. Example: UniProtKB:P07585-1, 31-359, Ser-34, MOD:00814|Asn-211/Asn-262/Asn-303, MOD:00160.

label.value: tumor necrosis factor ligand superfamily member 6 isoform FasL N-glycosylated 1

value.value: A tumor necrosis factor ligand superfamily member 6 isoform FasL glycosylated form that has been N-glycosylated at the Asn residues within the N-glycosylation sites located in the C-terminal extracellular region. Example: UniProtKB:P48023-1, Asn-184/Asn-250/Asn-260, MOD:00160.

definition.value: Category=modification. Note: This glycosylation does not appear to be required for receptor binding or biological activity.

label.value: tumor necrosis factor ligand superfamily member 6 isoform FasL soluble form

value.value: A tumor necrosis factor ligand superfamily member 6 isoform FasL that is the soluble N-terminal portion after ADAM10 processing.

A decorin isoform A that has been cleaved after the Phe residue within the F[NS]GLN motif as a result of the catabolic processing of decorin. This form lacks most of the leucine-rich domains and is abundant in adult skin tissue.

label.value: latent TGF-beta-binding protein 1 isoform 2, signal peptide removed form

value.value: A latent TGF-beta-binding protein 1 isoform 2 that has had the signal peptide removed. This form binds covalently to the latent associated peptide of the transforming growth factors through the third TB domain by disulfide bridging.

label.value: latent TGF-beta-binding protein 1 isoform 1, signal peptide removed form

value.value: A latent TGF-beta-binding protein 1 isoform 1 that has had the signal peptide removed. This form binds covalently to the latent associated peptide of the transforming growth factors through the third TB domain by disulfide bridging.

A mitogen-activated protein kinase 1 isoform 1 phosphorylated form that is phosphorylated at both Thr and Tyr of the TxY motif within the protein kinase domain. Example: UniProtKB:P28482-1, Thr-185, MOD:00047|Tyr-187, MOD:00048.

A mitogen-activated protein kinase 3 isoform 1 phosphorylated form that is phosphorylated at both Thr and Tyr of the TxY motif within the protein kinase domain. Example: UniProtKB:P27361-1, Thr-202, MOD:00047|Tyr-204, MOD:00048.

label.value: nodal protein isoform 1, signal peptide removed form

value.value: A nodal protein isoform 1 that has had the signal peptide removed to yield the mature protein.

A retinoblastoma-like protein 2 isoform 1 phosphorylated form in which the phosphorylation occurs during Go/G1-S phase progression. A retinoblastoma-like protein 2 isoform 1 phosphorylated form that has Cdk-dependent G1 phosphorylation, and additionally phosphorylated on a Ser residue within the region linking the retinoblastoma-associated protein A and B domains, by cyclin Cdk4(6). This phosphorylation leads to ubiquitin-dependent proteolysis.

A retinoblastoma-like protein 2 isoform 1 that has been phosphorylated on residues at positions equivalent to Ser-639, Ser-952, Ser-966, Ser-971, Ser-972, Ser-973, Thr-974, Ser-981, Ser-982, and Thr-986 of the amino acid sequence represented by UniProtKB:Q08999-1 or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. Example: UniProtKB:Q08999-1, Ser-639/Ser-952/Ser-966/Ser-971/Ser-972/Ser-973/Ser-981/Ser-982, MOD:00046|Thr-974/Thr-986, MOD:00047.

definition.value: Category=modification. Note: This form has been found significantly elevated in mouse myopathy model and human heart failure patients.

value.value: A Rho-associated protein kinase 2 isoform 1 that has been cleaved in the granzyme B consensus motif [IVL][GE]xD located between the Rho binding and the PH domains, removing the C-terminus.

definition.value: Category=modification. Note: This form has constitutive kinase activity.

value.value: A Rho-associated protein kinase 2 isoform 1 phosphorylated form in which the phosphorylation occurs within the C-terminal region by the action of serine/threonine-protein kinase PLK1.

definition.value: Category=modification. Note: Phosphorylation can occur at Ser and/or Thr residues.

value.value: A Rho-associated protein kinase 2 isoform 1 phosphorylated form that has been induced by DNA damage. Example: UniProtKB:O75116-1, Thr-1078, MOD:00047.

label.value: ribosomal protein S6 kinase beta-1 isoform 1 phosphorylated 1

value.value: A ribosomal protein S6 kinase beta-1 isoform 1 phosphorylated form in which the phosphorylation occurs within the AGC-kinase C-terminal domain. Example: UniProtKB:P23443-1, Ser-441/Ser-447, MOD:00046|Thr-444, MOD:00047.

definition.value: Category=modification. Note: AGC kinases are serine/threonine protein kinases. The phosphorylation sites serve as phosphorylation-regulated switches to control both intra- and inter-molecular interactions. Without these priming phosphorylations, the kinases are catalytically inactive.
